Recommendation/s:

We have recommended that the Bids and Awards Committee, who has the responsibility for ensuring that the procuring entity abides by the standards set forth by RA 9184 and its IRR, strictly adhere with all provisions of law, rules and regulations pertaining to procurements to protect at all times the interest of the local government unit. We further recommended that:

The procurement of goods which are similar in nature be consolidated and procured through  public bidding;

Conditions set forth by the law are strictly observed before resorting to alternative modes of procurement;  

Pre-bid conference be conducted for contracts to be bid with an approved budget of one million pesos (P1,000,000.00) or more;

Warranty security be required from the contract awardee after the performance of the contract in order to assure that manufacturing defects shall be corrected by the supplier in the case of procurement of goods and that responsibility for any damage or destruction of the works except those occasioned by force majeure in the case of procurement of infrastructure projects be established; and


Impose the ten percent (10%) retention on progress payments which can be used to cover uncorrected discovered defects and third party liabilities.

Recommendation/s:

We have recommended that the management strictly adhere with the policy guidelines and procedures in the implementation of Bottoms-up Budgeting programs. For the foregoing deficiencies, we have recommended the following:

The concerned officials and employees responsible for the implementation of BUB programs strictly adhere with the terms of the Memorandum of Agreement and contents of the approved project proposal/plan to avoid disallowance/suspension in audit;

The Associations be required to maintain records to ensure that the income generated from the two micro-enterprise projects will accrue to the benefit of the Associations and provide management, interested users or other oversight agencies of the vital information relative to operation of the two projects as well as evaluation of its operations;

Collection of the proceeds from the sale of the concrete hollow blocks be ensured by the Project Coordinator in order to sustain the operations/production activity of the Association;

The ICO-Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer ensure the completeness of supporting documents before affixing their signatures in the disbursement vouchers and before effecting payments pursuant to Section 4 (6) of Presidential Decree No. 1445 to avoid audit suspension or disallowances; and

The concerned officials submit the documents supporting the implementation of the Marketing activity as indicated in the approved project proposal/plan
